page.title: 10BIRDS OF WYCHWOOD FOREST
page.content: The 3 native {woodpeckers}- Greater Spotted, Lesser Spotted and Green - all nest in holes of rotten tree- trunks within the Forest. Many {Tree- {creepers and Nuthatches} can be seen by the silent bird watcher. {Warblers of several varieties have been seen. {Owls and nightingales} are more often heard than seen. Among the {water {birds }seen on the lakes within the forest and the park are {Herons, King- {fishers, Tufted Duck and Canada Geese. In recent years {Woodcocks }have begun to breed. Visiting or migrant birds sighted by a voluntary warden of the Nature Conservancy Council include {Osprey, Bitterns, Red Kite and Golden {Oriole}.
